Explanation:

- The controller method handling PATCH /admin/comments/{comment} is CommentController::update. It uses CommentsRequest for validation and then calls $comment->update(...) and returns redirect()->route('admin.comments.edit', $comment)->withSuccess(...).
- From the code and tests:
  - On successful update the endpoint performs an HTTP redirect (302 Found) to the edit page for that comment (Location header) and sets a flash success message in session. The tests assert a redirect to /admin/comments/{id}/edit.
  - On validation failure (CommentsRequest rules), Laravel automatically redirects back (also 302) with validation errors in session. The tests assert a 302 status and session errors are present.
  - If the comment cannot be resolved by route model binding (missing resource) the framework will return 404 Not Found.
- Therefore appropriate Response Objects for Swagger 2.0 are provided for the relevant status codes: 302 (covers successful update redirect and validation failure redirect; includes Location header) and 404 (resource not found). No response body schema is defined because the responses are redirects and errors are provided via session/flash in this web application.

